Class GenericPaginator<T extends Thing>

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.dean.jraw.paginators.Paginator<T>
      • net.dean.jraw.paginators.GenericPaginator<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of Thing that
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Iterator<Listing<T>>, NetworkAccessible<RedditResponse,RedditClient>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AllSubredditsPaginator, GenericUserRecordPaginator, InboxPaginator, ModeratorPaginator, UserContributionPaginator, UserSubredditsPaginator

    public abstract class GenericPaginator<T extends Thing>
extends Paginator<T>
    This class provides a template for Paginators that use only a "where" attribute, such as /user/username/{where}. The way this class assembles the base URI (getBaseUri()) works somewhat differently than other paginators. The formula for creating this URI is as follows: {prefix}{where.name().toLowerCase()}{postfix}. So if getUriPrefix() resulted in "/user/username/", the enum value's name was "SUBMITTED", and getUriPostfix() resulted in ".json", then the base URI would be "/user/username/submitted.json".
